<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10092918>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Specimens of the fossil stork Ciconia louisebolesae. (A) partial skull (QM F20910, Bitesantennary Site), lateral view; (B) right quadrate (QM F20893, Bitesantennary Site), lateral view; (C) proximal right humerus (QM F20911, Bitesantennary Site), posterior view; (D–E) distal right humerus (holotype: QM F30290, Bitesantennary Site), (D) anterior view, (E) posterior view; (F–G) proximal left tarsometatarsus (QM F36447, Wayne’s Wok Site), (F) anterior view, (G) lateral view; (H–I) distal right tarsometatarsus (QM F36446, Bitesantennary Site), (H) dorsal view, (I) plantar view. Scale = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10092918/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

